lessen /ˈlɛsən/

(lessening,lessened,lessens) 

1. V-T/V-I If something lessens or you lessen it, it becomes smaller in size, amount, degree, or importance. 减少; 降低; 减轻 

例： He is used to a lot of attention from his wife, which will inevitably lessen when the baby is born. 他习惯了妻子无微不至的关心，这种关心在孩子出生以后将不可避免地减少。 

2. lessening N-UNCOUNT 减轻 

例： ...increased trade and a lessening of tension on the border. …贸易的增加和边境紧张局势的减轻。

